Title: Model selection using wavelet decomposition and applications  
Author: Anestis Antoniadis Irene Gijbels Gerard Gregoire 
Address: BP 53, 38042 Grenoble Cedex, France B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium  BP 53, 38042 Grenoble Cedex, France  
Affiliation: Laboratoire LMC IMAG Institut de Statistique Universite Joseph Fourier Universite Catholique de Louvain  Laboratoire LMC IMAG Universite Joseph Fourier  
Abstract: In this paper we discuss how to use wavelet decomposition to select a regression model. The methodology relies on a minimum description length criterion which is used to determine the number of non-zero coe-cients in the vector of wavelet coef-flcients. Consistency properties of the selection rule are established and simulation studies reveal information on the distribution of the minimum description length selector. We then apply the developed model selection rule to a few testing problems, among which testing for pure white noise. The power of this test is investigated via simulation studies. Furthermore, the selection criterion is applied to testing for no efiect in nonparametric regression and for martingale structure in time series. 
